@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "MLink" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your
Workbench must have at least 8 colours.

NOTE: As I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that MLink runs fine
      on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with a
      68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  The game consists of 15 coloured chainlinks that were randomly
shuffled. You have to place these chainlinks in the right order,
obviously with the top ones (the upper 'semicircles') on the top,
the lower ones (the lower 'semicircles') below and the intermediate
links in between. Of course their colour must match in each
column...

  Note that you don't have to place the chains in a specific colour
order from left to right and the shorter chain can be placed either
in the upper or lower position in its column, as long as its links
are joined together.

  Playing with MLink is very simple: A chainlink can move up or
down if it is located under or over the empty space, clicking on it
will move the chainlink towards the empty space.

  You can also move all chainlinks on the upper or bottom rows. To
move chainlinks to the left, click on one of the 2 leftmost tiles,
and to move chainlinks to the right, click on one of the 2
rightmost tiles of the choosen row. If a chainlink or the empty
space is located on one edge, it will go to the other edge. Please
note that if you click on a chainlink located on the top or bottom
row and the empty space is located under or over that chainlink,
then the chainlink will go towards the empty space instead.

  Have fun!

  You can restart the game anytime by clicking on the @{b}New Game@{ub}
button.

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's
closebutton or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

